<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Project: Remote Trashcan | Jackson Nguyen</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Urbanist:wght@400;600;700&family=Azeret+Mono&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Urbanist', sans-serif; background-color: #0f172a; color: #e2e8f0; }
        .mono { font-family: 'Azeret Mono', monospace; }
        .accent-color { color: #DEFF9A; }
        .card-bg { background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.5); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="py-12">

    <nav class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
        <a href="../index.html" class="mono accent-color hover:underline text-sm uppercase tracking-widest">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left mr-2"></i> Back to Hub
        </a>
    </nav>

    <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold mb-4 uppercase">Remote Trashcan</h1>
            <p class="mono text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest">Personal Project | Embedded Systems</p>
        </div>

        <div class="w-full h-[400px] bg-slate-800 rounded-sm mb-16 overflow-hidden border border-white/5">
            <img src="../assets/TC-wiring prototype.jpg" class="w-full h-full object-cover" alt="Remote Trashcan Prototype">
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-16">
            <div class="space-y-10">
                <div>
                    <h4 class="mono text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Core Stack</h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                        <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-1"><span>Controller</span> <span class="accent-color">Arduino</span></li>
                        <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-1"><span>Input</span> <span class="accent-color">IR Receiver</span></li>
                        <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-white/5 pb-1"><span>Output</span> <span class="accent-color">Servo Motor</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <a href="https://github.com/JacksonAkt/Remote-Trashcan" target="_blank" class="block card-bg p-4 text-center hover:border-accent transition text-sm">
                    <i class="fa-brands fa-github mr-2"></i> Repository [cite: 13]
                </a>
            </div>

            <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-12">
                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-3 italic">
                        <span class="h-1 w-8 bg-accent"></span> System Concept
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                        Designed and built an Arduino-based trashcan lid mechanism controlled by an infrared remote[cite: 14]. This project focused on the seamless integration of sensor input, wiring, and mechanical movement into a functional prototype.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="card-bg p-8 border-l-2 border-accent">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Firmware Logic</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        Programmed the Arduino to accurately decode IR signals[cite: 15]. The logic translates specific remote button presses into precise PWM commands for the servo motor to orchestrate the opening and closing cycles of the lid[cite: 15].
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</body>
</html>